ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a great class! The texts are really interesting and fun (they are all about the creepy parts of the Underworld with many creatures that cut up souls and drink blood). Professor Darnell is a master of these texts and helps you to understand and link the multiple compositions together, all the while improving your Egyptian grammar skills! This is a terrific class!
I would, but obviously only if you're majoring or have learned Middle Egyptian.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course helped me to understand religious texts of the New Kingdom, and was a great complement to the religion class.
I am only an undergrad, but it was certainly amazing to be around the graduate students and listen to graduate-level discussion of the material.
